Caretaker Chairman in Iganna Local Council Development Area of Oyo State, Mr. Jacob Adeleke who was kidnapped a few days ago has regained freedom. DAILY POST recalls that the council boss and his driver were abducted last Sunday evening. Sources who confirmed the incident said the abduction had occurred along the Okeho-Ado Awaye Road. Our correspondent, however, gathered that the duo has regained their freedom. They were released on Friday evening. Police Public Relations Officer in the state, Mr. Olugbenga Fadeyi confirmed their release. “The chairman has regained his freedom and reunited with his family.”